5. Single-TBU INIU sys path is not compile-safe in dti_pr
- Priority: P1
- Category: RTL parameter edge-case blocker
- Trigger condition:
  - any macro-published *_iniu_sys instance that emits TBU_NUM=1
- Live generated evidence:
  - soc_dti_noc_demo/build_logic/gpu_iniu_sys/gpu_iniu_sys_macros_a0b3757ede.sv
  - soc_dti_noc_demo/build_logic/camera_iniu_sys/camera_iniu_sys_macros_a0b3757ede.sv
- Source owner to inspect:
  - subs/lwnoc_dti_noc/rtl/iniu/dti_pr.sv
- Root cause:
  - allocate_id and entry_reset_id are declared with $clog2(TBU_NUM)
  - the allocate/reset paths instantiate fcip_lead_one with ENTRY_NUM=TBU_NUM unconditionally
  - when TBU_NUM==1, the downstream FCIP onehot2bin helper chain can collapse to an illegal zero-width case
- Impact:
  - affects single-TBU INIU sys leaves such as gpu/camera/display/peri/npu/mipi/usb_dp/usb_ufs/dsp/pcie_eth
  - vpu_ss is outside this class because it emits TBU_NUM=2
- Suggested fix direction:
  - clamp the local entry-index width in subs/lwnoc_dti_noc/rtl/iniu/dti_pr.sv to at least 1 bit
  - add a TBU_NUM==1 special case for the allocate/reset lead-one path, or otherwise prove the FCIP helper chain is legal for ENTRY_NUM==1
- Status:
  - reported only; no sub repo code change was made in this session

